  "body": "<!-- This form is for bug reports and feature requests ONLY! \r\n\r\nIf you're looking for help check [Stack Overflow](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/tagged/kubernetes) and the [troubleshooting guide](https://kubernetes.io/docs/tasks/debug-application-cluster/troubleshooting/).\r\n-->\r\n\r\n**Is this a BUG REPORT or FEATURE REQUEST?**:\r\n\r\n> Uncomment only one, leave it on its own line: \r\n>\r\n> /kind bug\r\n> /kind feature\r\n\r\n\r\n**What happened**:\r\nContinue to https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/issues/55937\r\n\r\nI've tried to migrate from Gi to G and got stuck.\r\n\r\nHeketi creates volumes in GB ([api](https://github.com/heketi/heketi/wiki/API#volume_create)), it means 1024\\*1024\\*1024 ([src](https://github.com/heketi/heketi/blob/9d2ef4bbaf547f5b86055e935f1d583196a069f1/apps/glusterfs/volume_entry.go#L27)) or Gi in k8s format.\r\n\r\nSo, when I want pv/pvc with 50Gi (50\\*1024\\*1024\\*1024 bytes), gluster plugin parses it as 54G (54\\*1000\\*1000\\*1000 bytes) and than heketi creates volume as 54GB (54\\*1024\\*1024\\*1024 bytes).\r\n\r\ndf output means Gi too:\r\n\r\n```bash\r\n$ kubectl exec -it web-0 sh\r\n# df -hT      \r\nFilesystem                                    Type            Size  Used Avail Use% Mounted on\r\n10.0.0.5:vol_9b93bfd8c134ca081e1044c67d369cb3 fuse.glusterfs   54G   34M   54G   1% /usr/share/nginx/html\r\n\r\n# df --help \r\n...\r\nSIZE is an integer and optional unit (example: 10M is 10*1024*1024).  Units          \r\nare K, M, G, T, P, E, Z, Y (powers of 1024) or KB, MB, ... (powers of 1000).         \r\n...\r\n``` \r\n\r\nIt makes sense for my project. We take volume (as bytes), try to import it to k8s as pv and get such situation now:\r\n```\r\nvolume n*1024*1024*1024 bytes -> k8s N*1000*1000*1000 -> heketi/glusterfs N*1024*1024*1024\r\n```\r\nor\r\n```\r\nvolume n*GB(binary) -> k8s pvc n*Gi(binary) -> k8s pv N*G(decimal) -> glusterfs volume N*GB(binary)\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\n",
